The '''8D smelter droid''' (or '''8D Smelting Operator''') was a heavy industrial [[Droid/Legends|droid]] model manufactured by [[Roche Hive Mechanical Apparatus Design and Construction Activity for Those Who Need the Hive's Machines/Legends|Roche Hive Mechanical Apparatus Design and Construction Activity for Those Who Need the Hive's Machines]], a company founded by the [[Verpine/Legends|Verpine]] [[Species/Legends|species]] on the [[Roche asteroid field|Roche Asteroids]].

==Description==
[[File:8Dsmelter_egtd.png|thumb|left|180px|8D [[:Category:Technical drawing images|schematics]].]]
The 8D droid series resembled [[Muun/Legends|Muuns]] rather than their insectoid Verpine designers to suit the majority humanoid population of the Galaxy.<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Droids" /> They were distinguished by their rather long heads though the droid units seldom interacted with sentient beings once assigned to a job. Their attenuated limbs and complex leg joints were a trademark of their Verpine creators.<ref name="EGD">''[[The Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>

An 8D was designed to operate in smelting factories on worlds as varied as [[Aridus/Legends|Aridus]] and [[Balmorra/Legends|Balmorra]] where working conditions were too dangerous and hot for most sentient beings. Each body part was cast from high-grade [[Duravlex]]. This off-white substance's melting point was at over 4,000 degrees centigrade<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Droids" />, but the droids seldom worked in blast furnaces over 1,650 degrees centigrade.<ref name="EGD" />

Their photoreceptors were small and protected, giving the droid model quite weak eyesight. An 8D also was quite strong and possessed strong stamina though this came at the cost of the droids being rather sluggish. The 8D droids were programmed to have minimal intelligence, as their main tasks were simple labor, such as mining and smelting. The droids had crude personalities and a dislike for more intelligent units, and made a point to bully weaker droids whenever possible.

8Ds could be modified to act as damage control on starships by upgrading their [[Servomotor/Legends|servomotors]] for improved movement and equipping them a fire extinguisher and [[Tool kit/Legends|tool kit]].<ref name="SGD" />

==Operational history==
<div style="float:right">[[File:J0N0-EP.png|thumb|left|200px|[[J0-N0/Legends|J0-N0]] was a 8D smelter droid.]]</div>
The 8D smelter droid was manufactured and introduced into the heavy industrial market by Roche prior to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], following its debacle with the earlier [[J9 worker drone/Legends|J9 worker drone]]. Customers often found the droid to be tough, unfriendly and ill-tempered, crude and sluggish.

These droids participated in [[Nuna-ball/Legends|Nuna-ball]] leagues, and lost a game against [[Cybot Galactica/Legends|Cybot Galactica's]] [[CLL-6 binary load lifter droid|CLL-6 binary load lifter]] team in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].

One notable 8D Smelting Operator [[8D8/Legends|8D8]], also known as Atedeeate, served in [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure's]] [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|palace]]. At some point, he was modified to serve as a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] [[Maintenance droid/Legends|maintenance droid]], while under the sadistic tyranny of [[EV-9D9/Legends|EV-9D9]].

Following his migration to [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] employ on the sparse desert world of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], 8D8 was completely reprogrammed to serve as a dedicated torture droid&mdash;for both [[Droid/Legends|droids]] and [[Species/Legends|organics]]. Despite his programming, 8D8 retained a secret dislike for his taskmaster, EV-9D9.

[[Watto/Legends|Watto]] owned at least two droids of this model. They drove [[garbage grinder]]s in his junkyard.

